parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the radiator cooling system can cause hot coolant to spray onto the driver and passengers, resulting in severe burns and injuries.
symptoms: hot coolant spraying from under the dash
burning sensation on legs and feet.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine failure can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the timing chain can cause engine damage, stalling, and loss of power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The vehicle surges or lunges forward unexpectedly
even when the foot is on the brake
the vehicle accelerates while on cruise control
the vehicle has no control over idling speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the accelerator cable can cause loss of control over the vehicle's speed, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The plastic clip on the accelerator cable wears out prematurely
and the vehicle has no control over idling speed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the heater core can cause hot coolant to leak into the vehicle, resulting in serious burns to the driver and passengers, and potentially leading to accidents due to distraction or loss of control.
symptoms: Hot coolant or anti-freeze leaks onto the driver's legs or feet
and potentially causing the driver to lose control of the vehicle.
